{
  "id": "019cf638-6210-7ba0-9aa1-5b0c15038e93",
  "content": "# Persistent CUDA Embedding & Runtime Backend Fallback\n\n## Problem\nCUDA embedding failed because `libonnxruntime_providers_shared.so` wasn't on the system library path. Even after fixing library deployment, CUDA could fail at runtime (e.g., `cudaSetDevice` error 999 when GPU is in degraded state), causing the server to crash-loop.\n\n## Solution (commits 5ae12c5 + 548c7f7, 2026-03-16)\n\n### Library Deployment\n- `rebuild.py`: deploys `libonnxruntime_providers_cuda.so` alongside shared/openvino, runs `ldconfig` after install\n- `lib.sh`: `install_binaries()` downloads ORT provider .so from GitHub releases (best-effort — old releases without them don't break install)\n- `release.yml`: already ships provider .so files as release assets (from prior commit 8faec04)\n\n### Runtime Fallback Chain\n`embedding_service.rs::load_model()` now builds a fallback chain: CUDA → OpenVINO → CPU. If CUDA EP registers but session creation fails (cudaSetDevice, driver mismatch, etc.), it automatically retries with the next backend instead of returning an error that crashes the server.\n\n### Auto-Detect Config\n`corvia.toml` no longer hardcodes `backend = \"cuda\"` / `embedding_backend = \"openvino\"`. The `resolve_gpu_preferred()` auto-detect in `backend.rs` handles selection: CUDA > OpenVINO (embedding) > CPU. Explicit backend config returns errors on failure; auto-detect falls back gracefully.\n\n### CUDA Verification\n`verify_ep_available(BackendKind::Cuda)` now checks `can_find_library()` as a fallback after `can_dlopen()`, matching the OpenVINO pattern. Handles stale ldconfig cache.\n\n## Key Files\n- `repos/corvia/crates/corvia-inference/src/embedding_service.rs` — fallback chain, verification\n- `repos/corvia/crates/corvia-inference/src/backend.rs` — auto-detect logic (unchanged)\n- `tools/corvia-dev/corvia_dev/rebuild.py` — CUDA .so deploy + ldconfig\n- `.devcontainer/scripts/lib.sh` — ORT .so download from releases\n- `corvia.toml` — removed explicit backend overrides",
